“ The Voconian Law, passed during the later republic, 169 ss.c.‚ imposed a restriction on the institution of women as heirs. It applied only to large estates. A person whom the census placed in the first class, as having a rated property of at least 1003000 asses, was forbidden to appoint a woman as his heir. The alleged design os the statute is said to have been to restrain the growing luxury and extravagance of women by withholding strom them the means of being luxurious and extravagant on a large scale.
